  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>Changes in Cerebral Blood Flow due to the high or low fat yoghurt intake after 30 minutes and 120 minutes compared to a baseline measurement 30 minutes before yoghurt intake.</measure>
    <time_frame>30 minutes before as well as 30 minutes and 120 minutes after fat intake</time_frame>
    <description>We were interested in differential brain activations due to the high or low fat meal. To assess this, the mentioned time points are suitable.
The Cerebral Blood Flow is measured using Arterial Spin Labeling sequences in a functional magnetic resonance tomography.</description>
  </primary_outcome>
